Place the fish in a plastic food bag, add the soy, mirin and rice vinegar. Give it a good shake and refrigerate or freeze until ready to cook.Preheat the grill to its hottest setting and line a small roasting tin with foil. Drain the fish, reserving the marinade. Put the fish on the foil and grill for 5 minutes, or until cooked through.Meanwhile, heat a small wok or frying pan over a high heat and add the oil. Add the vegetables and stir-fry for 30 seconds. Add 2 tablespoons water and the reserved marinade and cook for 1â€“2 minutes, or until hot through.Place the vegetables on a warm plate and top with the fish. Scatter over the sesame seeds and coriander, if using.